    "user_reviews": [
      {
        "text": "I read reviews online for this particular card from Gigabyte and fan noise was the only complaint.\nDidn't believe how loud it would be until I played a game and even though the card wasn't hot (50degrees) the fans went to 100% and the noise was unbearable (and no, headphones noise cancelling or otherwise will not work, it's that loud).\n\nThe solution is to modify the fan curves with either the AMD software, or gigabyte software.\n\nNow it's running fine at 55-60 degrees playing Kingdom Come Deliverance 2 at 1440p ultra settings (100FPS on average).\n\nGood card for smaller cases as well, as it's much shorter than the other 9070XTs",
        "user_name": "ConanB77",
        "source": "pbtech.co.nz",
        "rating": 4,
        "date": "a year ago",
        "icon": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/shsm/AGYqVK1TV7L5tJ3PeS8crWs1rJZ6V8Pt0Jtt1MbjiLqaT9IVEwsC-IUfxobtr4JpgCFfE9C11w=w40-h40-c0x00000000-cc"
      },
      {
        "title": "Powerful, compact, and silent",
        "text": "Using it in a pair with Ryzen 7 5700x in a mini ITX case (NZXT H1v2), powered by Corsair PSU 750W\n\nKept all GPU setting without adjustments, cards is powerful and surprisingly silent. So far no hardware or driver issues. The only drawback is that I have little to less time to play video games 😭",
        "user_name": "Vsevolod",
        "source": "bhphotovideo.com",
        "rating": 5,
        "date": "4 months ago",
        "icon": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/shsm/AGYqVK1desAmMV7_x5n4MHwgCglekFO0jnCiFBGbxUvWOE6oq_Gx74Q0CzDJ9xQWNBLLsua7zg=w40-h40-c0x00000000-cc"
      },
      {
        "title": "Say hello to the highest value 9070 XT",
        "text": "I just upgraded from a 6700 XT to the AMD 9070 XT, and the jump in performance has been dramatic. At 3840x1600, I’m now seeing frame rates in the low to mid-100s, and at 1440p 16:9 they climb into the high-100s—everything feels buttery smooth.\n\nWhat really surprised me is how quiet it runs, basically silent even under load.\n\nI also had to upgrade my power supply since this version takes three PCIe connectors, but I actually like that it feels like the card is using the power it needs to really deliver.\n\nOn top of that, I’m really happy with the build quality. The backplate and cooler design give it a lot of rigidity, which matters since these cards are massive these days. Even though this is the cheapest version I could find, I honestly don’t see what more I’d want from a more expensive model.\n\nI’m getting max performance right out of the box. For me, it’s been the perfect upgrade: quiet, solidly built, and insanely fast compared to my old 6700 XT.",
        "user_name": "Matthew",
        "source": "bestbuy.com",
        "rating": 5,
        "date": "10 months ago",
        "icon": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/shsm/AGYqVK3v19vq5Y-IZgZLwytsposeOLrAIJgOw4fCkXMjNbPrHX3zvAfmiyMyd3izCIWJLX-Eng=w40-h40-c0x00000000-cc",
        "incentivized": true,
        "images": [
          "https://encrypted-tbn2.gstatic.com/shopping?q=tbn%3AANd9GcQMxZ2kKBoMkBTiMdGzqyffJtFPPZZJ9jV5pwrox3IuFtHMBfT7kyuYzGcf9xAc6icec5bM4U16KiBgzA1bizj91JAqwQXq-g"
        ]
      },
      {
        "title": "Great GPU",
        "text": "The RX 9070 XT is a great value proposition. I've had no driver issues or performance issues running 32:9 5120x1440. FSR4 performance is good, and the visual quality is great (slightly lagging behind dlss4 but on par or better than dlss3 IMO). Solidly better visual quality than XESS with way less of a performance hit, for reference.\n\nEven at nearly 4k resolution, this GPU keeps up in most titles. The 16GB of VRAM is maybe a concern long-term for 4k res, but if you're aiming for a fast 144hz+ 1440p card this is gonna be it for a while.\n\nOverall, this card is relatively quiet, has good cooling, good performance, and isn't too gaudy. Plus, it's not excessively long- attached is a comparison to my old 6800 xt and it's nearly an inch shorter (and half a slot less thick)",
        "user_name": "StevenB",
        "source": "bestbuy.com",
        "rating": 5,
        "date": "9 months ago",
