        "text": "Great overall GPU that performs really well. Mem and HotSpot temps can get up to high 80s but the card is still perfectly fine at those temps considering this is one of the shorter 9070XTs length wise. If the fans go above 50% speed it sounds like a jet taking off but my card never really needs to go above 40%. Got it to pass a Steel Nomad run with an Undervolt of -120 and a Mem Clock of 2774MHz, it scored 7997 points. -65 and 2714MHz is what I keep it at most of the time though because it's the highest I can go that is still stable in all of the games I've tried so far. FSR4 is really great as well, just wish AMD would push Devs to put it in games faster and let RX 7000 owners use it officially.",
